<i>&quot;It is not for nothing that the capital of Santa Catarina is known as the Island of Magic. The natural beauty of Florian&oacute;polis enchants at first sight. There are about a hundred beaches spread throughout the coastal island and the small continental peninsula forming the city. There are many other attractions to visit, as the beautiful and agitated Lagoa da Concei&ccedil;&atilde;o (Concei&ccedil;&atilde;o Lagoon), the peaceful Lagoa do Peri (Peri Lagoon), the traditional Centro Hist&oacute;rico (Historical Center), the cosmopolitan Avenida Beira-Mar (Seashore Avenue), the bucolic Azorean districts of Santo Ant&ocirc;nio de Lisboa and Ribeir&atilde;o da Ilha, besides Portuguese forts, museums, churches, theaters and the city postcard: the Herc&iacute;lio Luz Bridge.&quot; (SanTur - Santa Catarina Tourism Bureau)</i>
